🌐 Accessible & SEO-Friendly HTML5 Web Page
This project showcases a simple, accessible, and SEO-optimized web page built using semantic HTML5. It demonstrates best practices in web structure, accessibility, and search engine optimization, ideal for both learning and real-world implementation.

🧰 Features
✅ HTML5 Semantic Structure: Uses modern tags like <header>, <nav>, <main>, <section>, <article>, and <footer> for clear content organization.

♿ Accessibility-Friendly: Implements ARIA roles and accessible navigation to support users with disabilities and screen readers.

🔍 SEO Best Practices: Meta tags for description, keywords, and author to enhance search engine discoverability.

📱 Responsive Meta Tag: Ensures the page adapts well to different screen sizes.

